SIMPLE: mullion
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mullion
<hw>Mul"lion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A corruption of
<ets>munnion</ets>, F. <ets>moignon</ets> stump of an amputated limb,
stump, OF. <ets>moing</ets> mutilated; cf. Armor. <ets>mo⟦ntil⟧</ets>,
<ets>mou⟦ntil⟧</ets>, <ets>mank</ets>, <ets>monk</ets>, and also L.
<ets>mancus</ets> maimed.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A
slender bar or pier which forms the division between the lights of
windows, screens, etc.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>An upright member of a
framing. See <er>Stile</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mullion</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mullion
<hw>Mul"lion</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To furnish with mullions; to
divide by mullions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mullock</ent>⟦br⟧
